 your confidence, which makes you unique in your field leading you to be successful.\n\n- Alahdal\n|\nThe whales do not sing because they have an answer, they sing because they have a song.\n\n- Gregory\n|\nPassion gives you what you want, lust gives you what you desire, but only love gives you what you need.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nA philosopher is a lover and searcher of truth, beauty, meaning, and wisdom.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nWomen speak because they wish to speak, whereas a man speaks only when driven to speak by something outside himself-like, for instance, he can't find any clean socks.\n\n- Jean\n|\nFuture has a scheming, naughty and intelligent mind. It is never fully predictable!\n\n- Amit\n|\nYou must learn to take a step back and visualize the whole piece. If you focus only on the thread given to you, you lose sight of what it can become.\n\n- Colleen\n|\n(God) will always grant us wisdom when we ask. And when we seek Him and obey Him, He works all things out for our good.\n\n- Teresa Schultz, The Bible In Poetry,\n|\nIf you keep doing things that don't matter to you, you will not have time to do things that really do.\n\n- RVM\n|\nA great teacher is one that helps their students to become great. In return, the students appreciate the teacher for their success.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nHow much time he gains who does not look to see what his neighbour says or does or thinks, but only at what he does himself, to make it just and holy.\n\n- Marcus Aurelius, Meditations\n|\nThankfully, persistence is a great substitute for talent.\n\n- Steve Martin, Born Standing Up: A Comic's Life\n|\nNo matter how much experience you have, there’s always something new you can learn and room for improvement.\n\n- Roy T. Bennett, The Light in the Heart\n|\nIn the hearts of men lies both good and evil. The two coexist. Some men become good, and others become evil. It is the way of this world.-Kikyo\n\n- Rumiko\n|\nYou're always with yourself, so you might as well enjoy the company.\n\n- Diane\n|\nEducate every child to have a good head, good heart and kind spirit.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nFirst and foremost, God is the true hero of the story. No matter how captivating the other characters may be, our top priority is to discover what the Bible reveals about God.\n\n- Carolyn Custis James, The Gospel of Ruth: Loving God Enough to Break the Rules\n|\nPeople wonder who is who,Everyone is different - even you!\n\n- Christina Engela, Other Kids Are Kids Almost Just Like You\n|\nIf this is how you treat your friends, no wonder you have so many enemies.\n\n- Teresa\n|\nDon’t forget to collect the memories on your journey. Remember, if you only focus on your destination, you will miss out on the benefits of the journey.\n\n- Tanya R. Liverman, Journey to Legacy: A Poetic Timeline of My Life\n|\nBut though it had prevailed against such fierce adversaries as fire and flood, it had fallen victim softly and swiftly to television in the 1960's.\n\n- Kate Morton, The Forgotten Garden\n|\nIf you're a writer, the answer to everything is yes.\n\n- Nikki\n|\nIf while alive you hurt or disappoint people you love, there's no use continuing such behavior when you're dead.\n\n- Anthony Swofford, Jarhead\n|\nAnd if insight were sufficient, if the inner life were the whole of life, their happiness has been assured.\n\n- E.M.\n|\nShout out to everyone transcendinga mindset, mentality, desire, belief,emotion, habit, behavior or vibration,that no longer serves them.\n\n- Lalah\n|\nToday the world seems to be like a stagnated place, because the majority of humanity are not eager to see others rise.\n\n- Auliq-Ice\n|\nTruth is the preferred weapon of God, and censorship is the most abused tool of the Devil.\n\n- Suzy Kassem, Rise Up and Salute the Sun: The Writings of Suzy Kassem\n|\nYou can love a person dear to you with a human love, but an enemy can only be loved with divine love.\n\n- Leo Tolstoy, War and Peace\n|\nI want to know if we are the same, in the moments when we’re stripped bare.\n\n- Corey Ann Haydu, The Careful Undressing of Love\n|\nWe’re young, we’re not monsters, no fools: we’ll conquer happiness for ourselves.\n\n- Ivan\n|\nThe Bible is not religion, nor are the Vedas. The Torah is not religion, nor is the Quran, or any other scripture on earth.\n\n- Abhijit\n|\nSo a complex, by distorting our perception of ourselves in our mind, builds obstacles that prevent achievement of our goals\n\n- Sunday\n|\nWar, my friends, is a thing of beauty.\n\n- Mark  Lawrence, Prince of Thorns\n|\nThe harder you fall, the heavier your heart; the heavier your heart, the stronger you climb; the stronger you climb, the higher your pedestal.\n\n- Criss Jami, Killosophy\n|\nThe only things I regret, and the only things I'll ever regret are things I didn't do. In the end, that's what we mourn. The paths we didn't take. The people we didn't touch.\n\n- Scott Spencer, Endless Love\n|\nAh! well a-day! what evil looks Had I from old and young! Instead of the cross, the Albatross About my neck was hung.\n\n- Samuel Taylor Coleridge, The Rime of the Ancient Mariner\n|\nHow are we going to get out of here?''Oh, escape is easy once you have the right\n\n- Derek Landy, Death Bringer\n|\nSometimes success isn't about making the right decision, it's more about making some decision.\n\n- Robin S. Sharma, The Leader Who Had No Title: A Modern Fable on Real Success in Business and in Life\n|\nMen, I thought, were more trouble than they were worth. Really, one should stick to books where one sees the hero coming a mile off.\n\n- Eva Rice, The Lost Art of Keeping Secrets\n|\nWe avoid risks in life only to die, and end up facing the greatest risk which is having lived life risking nothing at all.\n\n- Chinonye\n|\nI wish I could think about nothing, but the books all the time. I have never had an alcoholic rampage because of thinking about books too much...\n\n- Robert\n|\nImagination is evidence of the divine, and the divine is the imagination of evidence.\n\n- Erik\n|\nWhat we want is not more little books about Christianity, but more little books by Christians on other subjects--with their Christianity latent.\n\n- C.S.\n|\nThis is only a work of fiction , The Truth as always will be far stranger\n\n- Arthur C. Clarke, 2001: A Space Odyssey\n|\nA halo surrounded the grim reaper nun, Sister Maria. (By the way-I like this human idea of the grim reaper. I like the scythe. It amuses me.)\n\n- Markus Zusak, The Book Thief\n|\nIn some sort of crude sense, which no vulgarity, no humor, no overstatement can quite extinguish, the physicists have known sin; and this is a knowledge which they cannot lose.\n\n- J.\n|\nवसुधा का नेता कौन हुआ?भूखंड-विजेता कौन हुआ?अतुलित यश-क्रेता कौन हुआ?नव-धर्म-प्रणेता कौन हुआ?जिसने न कभी आराम किया,विघ्नों में रहकर नाम किया\n\n- Ramdhari Singh 'Dinkar', रश्मिरथी\n|\nThe decision is your own voice, an opinion is the echo of someone else's voice.\n\n- Amit Kalantri, Wealth of Words\n|\nShe’s over the top rebellious,but damn her heart overflowing with insane love.She shakes thing up.Doesn’t play by rules and certainly fitsin nobody’s pretty perfect box.\n\n- Melody  Lee, Moon Gypsy\n|\nWe are flawed creatures, all of us. Some of us think that means we should fix our flaws. But get rid of my flaws and there would be no one left.\n\n- Sarah Vowell, Take the Cannoli\n|\nwaktu kita di bumi ini sakral adanya, dan kita seharusnya merayakan setiap detiknya\n\n- Paulo Coelho, The Witch Of Portobello\n|\nFar greater than all the material possessions that I possess, is my Freedom to Choose, my Freedom to Live, and my Freedom to be Happy.- RVM\n\n- RVM\n|\nNothing can enslaved us, if we free in our minds.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nDupa ce iti omori demonii, daca ai curajul sa o faci, e musai sa te intorci pe acelasi drum.\n\n- Tudor Chirilă, Exerciţii de echilibru\n|\nUltimately, nobody can get more out of things, including books, than he already knows.\n\n- Friedrich\n|\nThat's the problem with memories: you can visit them, but you can't live in them.\n\n- Shaun David Hutchinson, We Are the Ants\n|\nWomen have no appreciation of good looks-at least, good women have not.\n\n- Oscar Wilde, The Picture of Dorian Gray\n|\nThe truth was only another mask, even if it was the best fit, the closest to skin and all that lay beneath\n\n- Michelle Sagara West, The Broken Crown\n|\nSorry I'm late,' Ms. Egami said to the class. She dropped her papers, which scattered in that special way papers do when one is running late.\n\n- Adam Rex, Cold Cereal\n|\nTime: her heart wretched. What a useless thing, her mind growled. Only humans would be so arrogant and so stupid as to count down their own deaths.\n\n- Hunter Wilde, Erebus\n|\nFrugality, I've learned, has its own cost, one that sometimes lasts forever.\n\n- Nicholas Sparks, The Wedding"